OL,3,CBeach closed to swimmers due to
OL,4,Cpollution for fifth time in three weeks
OL,6,FIt is the fifth time that Exmouth
OL,7,Fbeach has been closed to swimmers due
OL,8,Fto pollution warnings since the
OL,9,Fbeginning of August.
OL,11,FAt the time, Paul Arnott, the leader
OL,12,Fof East Devon District Council,
OL,13,Fdescribed the spill and subsequent
OL,14,Fclosures as a "historic new low" for
OL,15,Fthe water company.
OL,17,FSouth West Water (SWW) said it was
OL,18,Fusing tankers to transport flows away
OL,19,Ffrom the burst location and was
OL,20,Finstalling an overland pipe as a
OL,21,Ftemporary solution.
